 was a man dressed in the color of night. Running, he held the hilt of his blade so that it would not hinder his movements nor make sound. Swiftly he disappeared into the shadows.<br><br>On the same cobblestone street there came others dressed in the same likeness. They stopped and danced around searching the area as if looking for the path taken by the first. Catching site of his direction via a splashed puddle, the others unsheathed their blades and hurried after him. <br><br>As the fleeing Rogue ran he took hold of his cloak and threw it to the ground. As he did a wind grabbed hold of it and gently it danced to the ground as the runner faded away into the darkness ahead. Again he entered a torch-lit street and stopped dead in his steps. Peering back into the darkness as he caught his breath.<br><br>Footsteps could be heard from beyond the shadows of the alley as his chasers neared. With a flash he dashed again into the alley and raced ahead. Entering the next street he took two small jumps and then with the third he flipped himself high into the air. His arms were extended out as were his legs in a pike form. The wind whistled as his body twisted slowly in the air. <br><br>He landed soundlessly on the shingles of a roof. There he ran and bounced from roof-top to roof-top until again he was unseen. Swallowed by the night leaving no trace to be found. <br><br>The others came at last to this spot and found the track to be lost. With much haste they combed the area and with the sound of approaching guards they too fled into the night. <br><br>As the moon gazed upon its self in the window of an old tavern on a forgotten side of town the lone rogue came running. Stopping to see if he had been fallowed he hastily checked his surroundings.<br><br>Seeing no one about he scaled the water drain on the side of the abandoned building and made his way to the window. Pushing it in, he climbed on to its ledge and peered into the darkness. There he saw…<br><br><br