ut the realization was too late.<br><br>&quot;I've been finding many Roses in my garden as of late.&quot;  Agile though he was, Shin could not avoid the large hand of Sir Galimont crashing through the window glass and pulling the stunned rescuer through the window and throwing him to the floor inside.  Shin reached for his daggers as he stood up, but a swift kick to the midsection and the half-unsheathed Nai-Toge was sent flying to one side of the room and Shin to the other.  Sir Galimont touched the scar on his chest lightly with his fingers.  &quot;I'll destroy your whole lot for this injustice...&quot;<br><br>Springing to his feet with the quickness of a jungle cat, Shin-Kai dodged several more attacks from Galimont and slipped past his monstrous body.  In a move that resembled a cartwheel, Shin recovered Nai-Toge from its resting place on the floor and returned to his ready position, this time much more able to take the offensive.  But before he could...<br><br>&quot;I'm no fool, I'll not risk my throat again against an assassin's blade.  Galimont snapped his fingers and from the door next to him, in walked three men, not as big as Galimont but big nonetheless and weilding swords.  One had a rather large two handed sword while the other two had shorter swords and a small buckler.  Shin-Kai prepared his mind for the worst, but before anyone had made a move, one of the shield wearing combatants lurched over dead!<br><br>Dropping in from the shadows of the rafters above, Veish'Kav Vittarlius landed without noise.  &quot;Hey Cajeline, long time no see.&quot;  He said without reverting his gaze from the remaining three warriors.  &quot;Got yer letter by the way...&quot;<br><br>The air stood still and the silece of the night was deafening.  Soon the only noise that was heard was the scurrying of rats in the walls and after many tense seconds...a voice.  &quot;Did I miss the party?&quot; a figure said stepping in from the corner of the room, from where there 