wo gold coins across the counter to the man, at the same time rushing toward the stairs and making certain his rapier was loose in its sheath.<br><br>Arriving at the top of the stairs, Arctyc stopped as he rammed into a man who's frame nearly filled the entire hallway.  &quot;Bloody Half-Giant!&quot;, he murmured.<br><br>&quot;Ey', whot you think you'r doin'?&quot;, the large figure asked, but before waiting for an answer, he unhooked the mace from his belt and swung.  Dancing back, Arctyc assumed then that he <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> didn't</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> want to play nice, and drew his own blade. <p><a href= "http://www.eqrogue.com"><img src= "http://members.theglobe.com/Arcti/AFRose.jpg"><br>Arctyc Foxfyre - "Don't cross me or my guild, lest you feel the stinging touch of <i>Rosa Spinus</i>, the Blackthorn Rose."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#460000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ucajeline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cajeline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#9C0000>(4/28/01 10:14:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fsbobrfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: There under the twilight...</span><hr size=1> “I WARNED YOU” Cajeline wanted to shout out, but was unable to.  Being as weak as she was. They had beaten her to find out why the mark was placed upon Lord Galimont’s  chest and what was the Rose after.. She was sure no one would come for her. She asked them not to. Knowing it was a trap and hearing the call of Shin. She wondered if he did not hear her words. Who was the bard in the Tavern who had received her rhyme and was he even her brother of the night.<br><br>She needed to warn them that the danger was far worse then what they were seeing, yes they could handle a few of these 